You can use API PyArg_ParseTuple function to extract the arguments from the one PyObject pointer passed into your C function.
The first argument to PyArg_ParseTuple is the args argument. This is the object you will be parsing. The second argument is a format string describing the arguments as you expect them to appear. Each argument is represented by one or more characters in the for

mat string as follows.

static PyObject *module_func(PyObject *self, PyObject *args) {
   int i;
   double d;
   char *s;

   if (!PyArg_ParseTuple(args, "ids", &i, &d, &s)) {
      return NULL;
   }

   /* Do something interesting here. */
   Py_RETURN_NONE;
}

